pageContext.claim: “Blame the Democrats for any 'lateness' in your Enhanced Unemployment Insurance. I wanted the money to be paid directly, they insisted it be paid by states for distribution. I told them this would happen, especially with many states which have old computers.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump never proposed federalizing the unemployment insurance program, which is administered by the states. His tweet appears to be an effort to shift anger away from one of his favorite governors, Ron DeSantis of Florida. In 2011, under a GOP governor, Florida imposed conditions that made it more difficult for people to collect unemployment benefits.
